Br. Impriſ 41. P.R. 14.36. Note alſo that the ſurety for the peace ſhall not be granted but where there is a feare of ſome preſent, or future danger, and not meerely for a batterie, or treſpaſſe that is paſt, or for any breach
of the peace that is paſt, for this ſurety of the peace is only for the ſecurity of ſuch as are in feare;
••••• metus, eſt preſentis vel futuri periculi cauſa mentis trepidatio, ſo this ſurety is providere praeſentia & futura, & non praeterita.
